$ to ${\\rm Re}\n\\sim 10^4$. Anisotropic transport may thus become negligible at high ${\\rm\nRe}$. Anisotropic viscosity nevertheless becomes the dominant source of heating\nat large ${\\rm Re}$, accounting for $\\gtrsim 50 \\%$ of the plasma heating. We\nconclude by briefly discussing the implications of our results for RIAFs onto\nblack holes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2019 19:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 Apr 2019 02:50:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-01"}
