escans prior to pathologist\nreview, potentially reducing the impact of digitization focus issues on the\nclinical workflow. We show that the algorithm trained on our semi-synthetic OOF\ndata generalizes well to real OOF regions across tissue types, stains, and\nscanners. Finally, quantitative OOF maps can flag regions that might otherwise\nbe misclassified by image analysis algorithms, preventing OOF-induced errors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Jan 2019 00:31:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2019 20:32:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-03"}
